The paper deals with a computational complexity problem related to polynomials and subsets of finite fields, which suggests that it belongs to the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of randomness in the problem also suggests that it may be related to information theory (cs.IT) or randomized algorithms (cs.DS). The study of subsets and their properties suggests that it may also be related to computational geometry (cs.CG) or discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
